<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>Created comprehensive documentation for the Todo System, addressing the missing documentation files referenced in the file location standardization changelog.</p>

<h2>Changes Made</h2>

<h3>1. Created Todo System Documentation</h3>

<p><strong>File Created:</strong> <code>/home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv/root/Documentation/features/todo_system.tt</code></p>

<p>This comprehensive documentation covers:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>System Architecture:</strong> Controller, Model, and Database Schema details</li>
    <li><strong>Database Structure:</strong> Complete field definitions and relationships</li>
    <li><strong>Available Routes:</strong> All 11 routes with parameters and features</li>
    <li><strong>Security Features:</strong> Access control and data validation</li>
    <li><strong>Integration Features:</strong> Project, User, Time Tracking, and Logging integration</li>
    <li><strong>Error Handling:</strong> Comprehensive error handling patterns</li>
    <li><strong>Performance Considerations:</strong> Database optimization and caching</li>
    <li><strong>Troubleshooting Guide:</strong> Common issues and debug mode usage</li>
</ul>

<h3>2. Documentation Structure</h3>

<p>The documentation follows the established Template Toolkit (.tt) format with:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Proper HTML comment with file path</li>
    <li>META title and PageVersion variables</li>
    <li>Debug mode conditional display</li>
    <li>Structured HTML markup with semantic elements</li>
    <li>CSS classes for styling consistency</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Content Coverage</h3>

<h4>System Components Documented</h4>
<ul>
    <li><code>Comserv::Controller::Todo</code> - Main controller with 11 actions</li>
    <li><code>Comserv::Model::Todo</code> - Business logic model</li>
    <li><code>Comserv::Model::Schema::Ency::Result::Todo</code> - Database schema</li>
</ul>

<h4>Routes Documented</h4>
<ol>
    <li><code>/todo</code> - Main todo list with filtering</li>
    <li><code>/todo/details</code> - Todo details view</li>
    <li><code>/todo/addtodo</code> - Add new todo form</li>
    <li><code>/todo/edit/{record_id}</code> - Edit todo form</li>
    <li><code>/todo/modify/{record_id}</code> - Update todo</li>
    <li><code>/todo/create</code> - Create new todo</li>
    <li><code>/todo/day/{date}</code> - Daily todo view</li>
    <li><code>/todo/week/{date}</code> - Weekly todo view</li>
    <li><code>/todo/month/{date}</code> - Monthly calendar view</li>
    <li><code>/todo/debug</code> - Debug information</li>
    <li><code>/todo/index</code> - Alternative index route</li>
</ol>

<h4>Database Schema</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Complete 24-field table structure</li>
    <li>Data types and constraints</li>
    <li>Relationship definitions (User, Project, Log)</li>
    <li>Primary and foreign key relationships</li>
</ul>

<h4>Features Documented</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Advanced Filtering:</strong> Date, project, status, and search filters</li>
    <li><strong>Time Tracking:</strong> Integration with Log system for accumulative time</li>
    <li><strong>Project Integration:</strong> Hierarchical project display and filtering</li>
    <li><strong>Security:</strong> Admin-only access with comprehensive session validation</li>
    <li><strong>Error Handling:</strong> Try/catch blocks with user feedback</li>
    <li><strong>Logging:</strong> Comprehensive logging using <code>log_with_details</code> method</li>
</ul>

